  "bug_report_content": "Title: NumberUtils createNumber throws a StringIndexOutOfBoundsException when argument containing \"e\" and \"E\" is passed in\nType: Bug | Priority: Major | Status: Closed | Resolution: Fixed\n\nDescription:\nNumberUtils createNumber throws a StringIndexOutOfBoundsException instead of NumberFormatException when a String containing both possible exponent indicators is passed in.\nOne example of such a String is \"1eE\".\n\nComments:\n\n[Ingo Heinrich]: Patch proposal fixing the bug.\n\n[Ingo Heinrich]: Patch to NumberUtilsTest.java for bug reproduction.\n\n[Henri Yandell]: svn ci -m \"Making it so that NumberUtils.createNumber throws a NumberFormatException instead of a StringIndexOutOfBoundsException when Strings such as 1eE are passed in. Thanks to Ingo Heinrich's report and patch in LANG-638\"\nSending        src/main/java/org/apache/commons/lang3/math/NumberUtils.java\nSending        src/test/java/org/apache/commons/lang3/math/NumberUtilsTest.java\nTransmitting file data ..\nCommitted revision 981736.",
